#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:344
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Uvod"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:346
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is \"&kwave;\", a simple sound editor built on the &kde-frameworks;. "
"Its features include:"
msgstr ""
"To je \"&kwave;\", preprost urejevalnik zvoka, zgrajen na &kde-frameworks;. "
"Njegove zmožnosti vključujejo:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:350
#, no-c-format
msgid "a user interface that can be switched to SDI, MDI or Tab mode"
msgstr ""
"uporabniški vmesnik, ki ga je mogoče preklopiti v način SDI, MDI ali Tab"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:353
#, no-c-format
msgid "simple cut, copy and paste functions"
msgstr "preproste funkcije izrezovanja, kopiranja in lepljenja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:356
#, no-c-format
msgid "multi-level undo/redo"
msgstr "razveljavi/ponovi na več ravneh"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:365
#, no-c-format
msgid "labeling of signals"
msgstr "označevanje signalov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:368
#, no-c-format
msgid "Recording functionality, including pre-recording"
msgstr "Funkcionalnost snemanja, vključno s pred-snemanjem"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:371
#, no-c-format
msgid "Playback via ALSA, PulseAudio, Qt, and OSS"
msgstr "Playback prek ALSA, PulseAudio, Qt in OSS"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:374
#, no-c-format
msgid "Recording via ALSA, PulseAudio, Qt, and OSS"
msgstr "Snemanje preko ALSA, PulseAudio, Qt in OSS"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:377
#, no-c-format
msgid "MP3 import/export"
msgstr "MP3 uvoz/izvoz"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:380
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ogg/Vorbis and Opus import/export"
msgstr "Ogg/Vorbis in Opus uvoz/izvoz"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:383
#, no-c-format
msgid "FLAC import/export"
msgstr "FLAC uvoz/izvoz"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:386
#, no-c-format
msgid "some analysis functions such as Sonagram"
msgstr "nekatere analitske funkcije, kot je Sonagram"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:389
#, no-c-format
msgid "internally uses 24 bit fixed precision for sample data"
msgstr "interno uporablja 24-bitno fiksno natančnost za vzorčne podatke"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:392
#, no-c-format
msgid "free selectable sample rates"
msgstr "proste izbirne stopnje vzorčenja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:395
#, no-c-format
msgid "support for editing of multi channel files"
msgstr "podpora za urejanje večkanalnih datotek"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:398
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"playback of multi channel audio files (audio output will be mixed down to "
"mono or stereo if needed)"
msgstr ""
"predvajanje večkanalnih zvočnih datotek (zvočni izhod bo po potrebi zmešan v "
"mono ali stereo)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:402
#, no-c-format
msgid "extendible through an easy-to-use plugin interface"
msgstr "razširljiv prek vmesnika vtičnika, ki je enostaven za uporabo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:405
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"import/export of other audio formats through <ulink url=\"&url_libaudiofile;"
"\">audiofile</ulink>"
msgstr ""
"uvoz/izvoz drugih zvočnih formatov prek <ulink url=\"&url_libaudiofile;"
"\">zvočne datoteke</ulink>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:412
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are interested what has been done and what has still to be done, then "
"look at the files <filename>CHANGES</filename> and <filename>TODO</filename> "
"included in the source package. Help and constructive critics are always "
"welcome."
msgstr ""
"Če vas zanima, kaj je bilo narejeno in kaj je še treba storiti, si oglejte "
"datoteki <filename>CHANGES</filename> in <filename>TODO</filename>, "
"vključeni v izvorni paket. Pomoč in konstruktivne kritike so vedno "
"dobrodošli."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:424
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kwave; Resources"
msgstr "&kwave; Viri"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:426
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"So if you want to get in contact with the developers, need some further help "
"on using &kwave;, submit patches, bug reports or other stuff, the following "
"resources might be of interest for you:"
msgstr ""
"Torej, če želite stopiti v stik z razvijalci, potrebujete dodatno pomoč pri "
"uporabi &kwave;, predložiti popravke, poročila o napakah ali druge stvari, "
"bi vas morda zanimali naslednji viri:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:433
#, no-c-format
msgid "Project Homepage<anchor id=\"project-homepage\"/>"
msgstr "Domača stran projekta<anchor id=\"project-homepage\"/>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:434
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For information about new up-to-date releases see the <ulink url="
"\"&url_apps_kde;\">&kwave; page</ulink> on apps.kde.org. For other "
"information take a look at the <ulink url=\"&url_homepage;\">&kwave; "
"homepage</ulink> ."
msgstr ""
"Za informacije o novih posodobljenih izdajah glejte <ulink url="
"\"&url_apps_kde;\">&kwave; strani</ulink> na apps.kde.org. Za druge "
"informacije si oglejte <ulink url=\"&url_homepage;\">&kwave; domačo stran</"
"ulink> ."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:440
#, no-c-format
msgid "Git Repository<anchor id=\"git-repository\"/>"
msgstr "Repozitorij GIT<anchor id=\"git-repository\"/>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:443
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The git repository is hosted on &kde;'s Gitlab instance <ulink url="
"\"&url_git_web_kde;\">here</ulink>, and there is also a mirror repository on "
"<ulink url=\"&url_git_web_sf;\">SourceForge</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Skladišče git gostuje v pojavku Gitlab &kde; <ulink url=\"&url_git_web_kde;"
"\">tukaj</ulink>, na <ulink url=\"&url_git_web_sf;\">SourceForge</ulink> pa "
"je tudi zrcalno skladišče."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:458
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kwave; Revision History"
msgstr "&kwave; pregled zgodovine"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:460
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This project has been started by Martin Wilz in summer 1998 and has been "
"developed and improved by him and some other people. In November 1999 Thomas "
"Eschenbacher has started to fix some little bugs here and there and stepped "
"into the source code of the program deeper and deeper. Up to today he has "
"extended, rewritten or revised nearly every component of the program and "
"spent much time on improving it."
msgstr ""
"Ta projekt je poleti 1998 začel Martin Wilz, razvili in izboljšali pa so ga "
"on in nekateri drugi ljudje. Novembra 1999 je Thomas Eschenbacher tu in tam "
"začel popravljati nekaj majhnih napak in vedno globlje stopal v izvorno kodo "
"programa. Do danes je razširil, prepisal ali revidiral skoraj vsako "
"komponento programa in porabil veliko časa za njegovo izboljšavo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:470
