#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:497
#, no-c-format
msgid "Basics about digital audio"
msgstr "Osnove digitalnega zvoka"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:499
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter should give a short introduction about the basics of digital "
"audio processing, without going too much into details."
msgstr ""
"To poglavje bi moralo podati kratek uvod v osnove obdelave digitalnega "
"zvoka, ne da bi se spuščali preveč v podrobnosti."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:505
#, no-c-format
msgid "The analogue world"
msgstr "Analogni svet"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:507
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"First of all, one must know that the world is <emphasis>analogue</emphasis> "
"- but computers work <emphasis>digitally</emphasis>. So there are several "
"ways to convert analogue audio to digital audio and back again. As the way "
"from digital to analogue normally is the reversion of the way from analogue "
"to digital, we only describe the way from analogue to digital."
msgstr ""
"Najprej je treba vedeti, da je svet <emphasis>analogen</emphasis> – vendar "
"računalniki delujejo <emphasis>digitalno</emphasis>. Torej obstaja več "
"načinov za pretvorbo analognega zvoka v digitalni zvok in nazaj. Ker je pot "
"od digitalnega k analognemu običajno povratna pot od analognega k "
"digitalnemu, opisujemo le pot od analognega k digitalnemu."

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:521
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Conversion from sound to bits</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Pretvorba zvoka v bite</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:524
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>Conversion from sound to bits</para>"
msgstr "<para>Pretvorba zvoka v bite</para>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:526
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before continuing, analogue audio has to be transformed into electronic "
"signals in order to find its way into a computer. One common way to do this "
"is by using a microphone and an amplifier. This combination gets sound "
"(changes of air pressure) at its input and a voltage at its output. Higher "
"amplitude of the pressure changes will be represented by higher voltages at "
"the amplifier's output. This output is also called a <emphasis>'signal'</"
"emphasis>. Instead of a microphone you can of course also imagine other "
"sources of audio. And the \"amplifier\" can be the one that is integrated "
"into your sound card, where you normally cannot see it."
msgstr ""
"Preden nadaljujemo, je treba analogni zvok pretvoriti v elektronske signale, "
"da bi lahko našel pot v računalnik. Eden pogostih načinov za to je uporaba "
"mikrofona in ojačevalnika. Ta kombinacija dobi zvok (spremembe zračnega "
"tlaka) na svojem vhodu in napetost na svojem izhodu. Večjo amplitudo "
"sprememb tlaka bodo predstavljale višje napetosti na izhodu ojačevalnika. Ta "
"izhod se imenuje tudi <emphasis>'signal'</emphasis>. Namesto mikrofona si "
"seveda lahko omislite tudi druge vire zvoka. In \"ojačevalnik\" je lahko "
"tisti, ki je integriran v vašo zvočno kartico, kjer ga običajno ne vidite."

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:543
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Conversion to electronic signal</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Pretvorba v elektronski signal</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:546
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>Conversion to electronic signal</para>"
msgstr "<para>Pretvorba v elektronski signal</para>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:548
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"At this stage, the electrical signal has three limitations that one should "
"keep in mind:"
msgstr ""
"Na tej stopnji ima električni signal tri omejitve, ki jih je treba "
"upoštevati:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:552
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <emphasis>amplitude</emphasis> (volume) is limited to some maximum "
"level. This is a consequence of the electronic (amplifiers) that are only "
"able to handle voltages within some specific range. That's no problem as "
"long as sounds are not too loud. In that case the signal would be "
"<emphasis>clipped</emphasis>, which means that the electrical signal will "
"run against its margins and the result will be disturbed."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Amplituda</emphasis> (glasnost) je omejena na neko največjo raven. "
"To je posledica elektronike (ojačevalnikov), ki je sposobna obvladovati le "
"napetosti v določenem območju. To ni problem, dokler zvoki niso preglasni. V "
"tem primeru bi bil signal <emphasis>izrezan</emphasis>, kar pomeni, da bo "
"električni signal tekel proti svojim robom in rezultat bo moten."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:562
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <emphasis>frequency range</emphasis> is also limited. Due to the "
"mechanical constrains of microphones and the limited frequency range of "
"amplifiers, a signal's frequency range is limited. There are no hard borders "
"besides which the sound abruptly disappears, but below some low and above "
"some higher frequency the amplitude of the signal starts to decrease more "
"and more. The existence of a maximum frequency can be easily understood as a "
"limited speed of the electrical signal to rise and fall. By using high "
"quality amplifiers and microphones, the limits can be spread into ranges "
"where the human ear is no longer able to hear their results and thus get out "
"of interest. The human ear normally is not able to hear sound above 20 kHz."
msgstr ""
"Omejeno je tudi <emphasis>frekvenčno območje</emphasis>. Zaradi mehanskih "
"omejitev mikrofonov in omejenega frekvenčnega območja ojačevalnikov je "
"frekvenčno območje signala omejeno. Trdih meja, poleg katerih zvok nenadoma "
"izgine, ni, ampak pod neko nizko in nad neko višjo frekvenco začne amplituda "
"signala vedno bolj padati. Obstoj največje frekvence je mogoče enostavno "
"razumeti kot omejeno hitrost dviga in padca električnega signala. Z uporabo "
"visokokakovostnih ojačevalnikov in mikrofonov se lahko meje razširijo v "
"obsege, kjer človeško uho ne more več slišati njihovih rezultatov in tako "
"izgine iz zanimanja. Človeško uho običajno ne more slišati zvoka nad 20 kHz."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:577
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The signal contains <emphasis>noise</emphasis>. Noise is the most ugly enemy "
"of everyone who has to handle audio signals in any way. Noise is a typical "
"analogue effect, that makes the audio signal \"unsharp\" and disturbed, it "
"is always present and cannot be avoided. One can only try to use high "
"quality components that produce as low noise as possible, so that one cannot "
"hear it. Normally noise has a certain volume, so that the interesting sound "
"should be much louder in comparison to the noise. This is called the "
"<emphasis>signal to noise ratio (SNR)</emphasis>, the higher it is the "
"better the sound's quality will be. Sounds that have lower volume than the "
"noise cannot be heart."
msgstr ""
"Signal vsebuje <emphasis>šum</emphasis>. Šum je najhujši sovražnik vseh, ki "
"se kakorkoli srečujejo z zvočnimi signali. Šum je tipičen analogni učinek, "
"zaradi katerega je zvočni signal \"neoster\" in moteč, vedno je prisoten in "
"se mu ne moremo izogniti. Poskušamo lahko le uporabiti visokokakovostne "
"komponente, ki proizvajajo čim manj šuma, da ga ne slišimo. Običajno ima šum "
"določeno glasnost, tako da mora biti zanimiv zvok veliko glasnejši v "
"primerjavi s šumom. To se imenuje <emphasis>razmerje med signalom in šumom "
"(SNR)</emphasis>; višje kot je, boljša bo kakovost zvoka. Zvoki, katerih "
"glasnost je nižja od šuma, ne morejo biti srce."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:596
#, no-c-format
msgid "Digitalization"
msgstr "Digitalizacija"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:598
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When we want to store and play audio in a computer, we must convert the "
"analogue sound into digital data first. This process is called "
"<emphasis>digitalization</emphasis>. It converts an electronic signal into a "
"sequence of digital values."
msgstr ""
"Ko želimo zvok shraniti in predvajati v računalniku, moramo analogni zvok "
"najprej pretvoriti v digitalne podatke. Ta proces se imenuje "
"<emphasis>digitalizacija</emphasis>. Elektronski signal pretvori v zaporedje "
"digitalnih vrednosti."

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:609
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Digitalization of the electronic signal</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Digitalizacija elektronskega signala</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:612
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>Digitalization of the electronic signal</para>"
msgstr "<para>Digitalizacija elektronskega signala</para>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:614
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The conversion can be understood as a repetitive measurement of the "
"electronic signal's value at certain time, thus taking a <emphasis>sample</"
"emphasis> of the signal. The result is then encoded as a digital value."
msgstr ""
"Pretvorbo lahko razumemo kot ponavljajoče se merjenje vrednosti "
"elektronskega signala ob določenem času, s čimer vzamemo <emphasis>vzorec</"
"emphasis> signala. Rezultat se nato kodira kot digitalna vrednost."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:620
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The sampling could be done in arbitrary distances or in constant intervals. "
"The later method is much easier to handle, and thus it is normally used, "
"with a constant rate - the so-called <emphasis>sample rate</emphasis>. Usual "
"sample rates are 8000, 11025, 22050, and 44100 samples per second. In "
"practice sample rates are also given as frequencies, in Hz or kHz."
msgstr ""
"Vzorčenje se lahko izvaja v poljubnih razdaljah ali v stalnih intervalih. "
"Kasnejša metoda je veliko lažja za uporabo, zato se običajno uporablja s "
"konstantno hitrostjo - tako imenovano <emphasis>hitrost vzorčenja</"
"emphasis>. Običajne hitrosti vzorčenja so 8000, 11025, 22050 in 44100 "
"vzorcev na sekundo. V praksi so stopnje vzorčenja podane tudi kot frekvence "
"v Hz ali kHz."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:628
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The sample rate limits the highest frequency a digitized signal can "
"represent. Due to Shannon's theorem the highest usable frequency is half of "
"the sample rate, so with 44.1 kHz sample rate you cannot sample signals with "
"more than 22 kHz. To avoid a violation of that half-sample rate rule, your "
"soundcard already has built-in filters that filter away frequencies that are "
"higher than half of the used sample rate."
msgstr ""
"Hitrost vzorčenja omejuje najvišjo frekvenco, ki jo lahko predstavlja "
"digitaliziran signal. Zaradi Shannonovega izreka je najvišja uporabna "
"frekvenca polovica hitrosti vzorčenja, tako da s hitrostjo vzorčenja 44,1 "
"kHz ne morete vzorčiti signalov z več kot 22 kHz. Da bi se izognili kršitvi "
"tega pravila polovične stopnje vzorčenja, ima vaša zvočna kartica že "
"vgrajene filtre, ki filtrirajo frekvence, ki so višje od polovice "
"uporabljene hitrosti vzorčenja."

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:642
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Sampled signal</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Vzorčen signal</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:645
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>Sampled signal</para>"
msgstr "<para>Vzorčen signal</para>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:649
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sample Encoding"
msgstr "Kodiranje vzorca"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:651
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The result of the digital sampling process is a sequence of single "
"<emphasis>samples</emphasis>. One sample is a digital representation of a "
"signal's value at a certain time."
msgstr ""
"Rezultat postopka digitalnega vzorčenja je zaporedje posameznih "
"<emphasis>vzorcev</emphasis>. En vzorec je digitalna predstavitev vrednosti "
"signala v določenem času."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:656
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The value of a sample can be interpreted and encoded in several ways. The "
"simplest one is <emphasis>linear</emphasis> encoding. This means that each "
"sample's value directly represents the analogue signal's value multiplied "
"with a constant factor. This is easy to handle, but has the disadvantage "
"that noise will be audible especially on low amplitudes, where it disturbs "
"most, and less audible on high amplitudes, where it is less audible."
msgstr ""
"Vrednost vzorca je mogoče interpretirati in kodirati na več načinov. "
"Najenostavnejše je <emphasis>linearno</emphasis> kodiranje. To pomeni, da "
"vrednost vsakega vzorca neposredno predstavlja vrednost analognega signala, "
"pomnoženo s konstantnim faktorjem. To je preprosto za obvladovanje, vendar "
"ima to pomanjkljivost, da bo šum slišen zlasti pri nizkih amplitudah, kjer "
"najbolj moti, in manj slišen pri visokih amplitudah, kjer je manj slišen."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:665
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"One way to reduce the influence of noise is <emphasis>non-linear</emphasis> "
"encoding. This means that lower amplitudes are amplified before processing. "
"As lower amplitudes are amplified, their distance from noise increases and "
"the quality improves. The most common methods for this are <emphasis>A-Law</"
"emphasis> and <emphasis>U-Law</emphasis> encoding - some standardized "
"logarithmic amplification curves, used in digital telephony (ITU G.711 "
"standard)."
msgstr ""
"Eden od načinov za zmanjšanje vpliva šuma je <emphasis>nelinearno</emphasis> "
"kodiranje. To pomeni, da se nižje amplitude pred obdelavo ojačajo. Ko se "
"nižje amplitude ojačajo, se njihova oddaljenost od šuma poveča in kakovost "
"se izboljša. Najpogostejši metodi za to sta kodiranje <emphasis>A-Law</"
"emphasis> in <emphasis>U-Law</emphasis> – nekaj standardiziranih "
"logaritemskih ojačitvenih krivulj, ki se uporabljajo v digitalni telefoniji "
"(standard ITU G.711)."

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:679
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Nonlinear Encoding</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Nelinearno kodiranje</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:682
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>Nonlinear Encoding</para>"
msgstr "<para>Nelinearno kodiranje</para>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:685
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sample Formats"
msgstr "Vzorčni formati"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:687
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Samples can be stored in different formats and precisions. The most common "
"ones are integer (fixed-point) formats, that store values with "
"<emphasis>fixed quantisations</emphasis>. Depending on where the zero line "
"is defined, it has to be destinguished between <emphasis>unsigned</emphasis> "
"(only positive values, \"zero line\" is at half of the numeric range) and "
"<emphasis>signed</emphasis> (positive and negative values) integer formats."
msgstr ""
"Vzorce je mogoče shraniti v različnih oblikah in natančnostih. Najpogostejši "
"so celoštevilski formati (s fiksno točko), ki shranjujejo vrednosti s "
"<emphasis>fiksnimi kvantizacijami</emphasis>. Odvisno od tega, kje je "
"definirana ničelna črta, jo je treba razločevati med "
"<emphasis>nepredznačenimi</emphasis> (samo pozitivne vrednosti, »ničelna "
"črta« je na polovici številskega obsega) in <emphasis>predznačenimi</"
"emphasis> (pozitivne in negativne vrednosti) celoštevilskimi oblikami."

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:702
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Signed Format</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Predznačna oblika</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:705
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>Signed Format</para>"
msgstr "<para>Predznačena oblika</para>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:711
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Unsigned Format</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Nepredznačena oblika</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:714
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>Unsigned Format</para>"
msgstr "<para>Nepredznačena oblika</para>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:715
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As the quantisation loses some accuracy, it produces noise, the so-called "
"<emphasis>quantisation noise</emphasis>. That kind of noise has more effect "
"on low amplitudes, so this method of storing samples is not optimal, but "
"quite easy and very fast to handle (computers are fast in calculating with "
"fixed point numbers)."
msgstr ""
"Ker kvantizacija izgubi nekaj natančnosti, proizvaja šum, tako imenovani "
"<emphasis>kvantizacijski šum</emphasis>. Takšen šum bolj vpliva na nizke "
"amplitude, zato ta način shranjevanja vzorcev ni optimalen, je pa dokaj "
"enostaven in zelo hiter (računalniki so hitri pri računanju s števili s "
"fiksnimi točkami)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:723
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The second way of encoding samples is with <emphasis>floating point</"
"emphasis> numbers. With floating point numbers, noise is spread nearly equal "
"over all ranges of amplitudes and has advantages especially on low "
"amplitudes. However, this format is much slower when used for processing "
"(computers are much slower on calculating with floating point values in "
"comparison to fixed point numbers)."
msgstr ""
"Drugi način kodiranja vzorcev je s števili s <emphasis>plavajočo vejico</"
"emphasis>. Pri številih s plavajočo vejico je šum skoraj enakomerno "
"porazdeljen po vseh razponih amplitud in ima prednosti zlasti pri nizkih "
"amplitudah. Vendar je ta oblika veliko počasnejša, če se uporablja za "
"obdelavo (računalniki veliko počasneje računajo z vrednostmi s plavajočo "
"vejico v primerjavi s števili s fiksno vejico)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:731
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kwave; internally uses <emphasis>signed integer</emphasis> format with 24 "
"bit precision, stored in 32 bit integers. This has the disadvantage of "
"higher memory consumption when processing files with lower precision (&eg; 8 "
"bits), but processing 32 bit numbers is very fast and also leaves some "
"reserves for internal calculations, as only 24 bits are normally used."
msgstr ""
"&kwave; interno uporablja format <emphasis>celo predznačeno število</"
"emphasis> s 24-bitno natančnostjo, shranjeno v 32-bitnih celih številih. "
"Pomanjkljivost tega je večja poraba pomnilnika pri obdelavi datotek z nižjo "
"natančnostjo (&eg; 8 bitov), vendar je obdelava 32-bitnih števil zelo hitra "
"in pušča tudi nekaj rezerve za notranje izračune, saj se običajno uporablja "
"samo 24 bitov."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:749
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using &kwave;"
msgstr "Uporaba &kwave;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:750
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here is a little screenshot of the &kwave; main window, so that you get an "
"impression what &kwave; looks like..."
msgstr ""
"Tukaj je majhen posnetek zaslona &kwave; glavno okno, da dobite vtis, kako "
"je videti &kwave;..."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:756
#, no-c-format
msgid "Here's a screenshot of &kwave;"
msgstr "Tukaj je posnetek zaslona &kwave;"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:764
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the Main Window"
msgstr "Posnetek zaslona glavnega okna"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:773
#, no-c-format
msgid "User Interface Mode"
msgstr "Način uporabniškega vmesnika"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:775
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Depending on your personal preferences or use cases you can configure how "
"&kwave; handles multiple open files. You can switch this setting on the fly "
"through the menu <menuchoice> <guimenu>Settings</guimenu><guimenuitem>Show "
"Files in...</guimenuitem> </menuchoice>."
msgstr ""
"Glede na vaše osebne nastavitve ali primere uporabe lahko konfigurirate, "
"kako &kwave; obravnava več odprtih datotek. To nastavitev lahko sproti "
"preklopite v meniju <menuchoice> <guimenu>Nastavitve</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Pokaži datoteke v...</guimenuitem> </menuchoice>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:784
#, no-c-format
msgid "The three possible settings are:"
msgstr "Tri možne nastavitve so:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:789
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenuitem>Separate Windows (SDI)</guimenuitem>: When using the "
"<emphasis>Single Document Interface</emphasis> (SDI), each file will be "
"shown in a separate main window."
msgstr ""
"<guimenuitem>Ločena okna (SDI)</guimenuitem>: Ko uporabljate "
"<emphasis>vmesnik z enim dokumentom</emphasis> (SDI), bo vsaka datoteka "
"prikazana v ločenem glavnem oknu."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:793
#, no-c-format
msgid "screenshot of &kwave; in SDI mode"
msgstr "posnetek zaslona &kwave; v načinu SDI"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:801
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of SDI mode"
msgstr "Posnetek zaslona načina SDI"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:809
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenuitem>Same Window (MDI)</guimenuitem>: When using the <emphasis>Multi "
"Document Interface</emphasis> (MDI), there is only one &kwave; main window, "
"but within this window you have an area which shows sub-windows, which can "
"be resized, moved, tiled, cascaded or minimized."
msgstr ""
"<guimenuitem>Isto okno (MDI)</guimenuitem>: Pri uporabi <emphasis>Multi "
"Document Interface</emphasis> (MDI) obstaja samo en &kwave; glavno okno, "
"vendar imate znotraj tega okna območje, ki prikazuje podokna, ki jim je "
"mogoče spreminjati velikost, premikati, razlagati po ploščicah, kaskadirati "
"ali pomanjšati."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:815
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can select a window from the <guimenu>Window</guimenu> menu or cycle "
"through the sub-windows with <keycombo>&Ctrl;&Tab;</keycombo>."
msgstr ""
"Izberete lahko okno iz menija <guimenu>Okno</guimenu> ali se pomikate med "
"podokni s <keycombo>&Ctrl;&Tab;</keycombo>."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:820
#, no-c-format
msgid "screenshot of &kwave; in MDI mode"
msgstr "posnetek zaslona &kwave; v načinu MDI"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:828
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of MDI mode"
msgstr "Posnetek zaslona načina MDI"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:836
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenuitem>Tabs</guimenuitem>: This is a variant of the MDI interface, "
"where files are shown within separate tabs. You may know this mode from some "
"popular Internet browsers."
msgstr ""
"<guimenuitem>Zavihki</guimenuitem>: To je različica vmesnika MDI, kjer so "
"datoteke prikazane znotraj ločenih zavihkov. Ta način morda poznate iz "
"nekaterih priljubljenih internetnih brskalnikov."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:841
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can activate a tab via the <guimenu>Window</guimenu> menu or cycle "
"through the tabs with <keycombo>&Ctrl;&Tab;</keycombo>."
msgstr ""
"Zavihek lahko aktivirate prek menija <guimenu>Okno</guimenu> ali pa krožite "
"med zavihki s <keycombo>&Ctrl;&Tab;</keycombo>."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:846
#, no-c-format
msgid "screenshot of &kwave; in TAB mode"
msgstr "posnetek zaslona &kwave; v načinu TAB"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:854
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of TAB mode"
msgstr "Posnetek zaslona načina TAB"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:869
#, no-c-format
msgid "Command Line"
msgstr "Ukazna vrstica"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:871
#, no-c-format
msgid "List of Files or Commands"
msgstr "Seznam datotek ali ukazov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:872
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you start &kwave; from the command line, you can specify a list of files "
"that should be opened. The first specified file will be opened first, then "
"the other files. Each file will be opened in an own new window or sub-window "
"of the same &kwave; instance. If you specify wildcards, you can open a large "
"number of files at once."
msgstr ""
"Če zaženete &kwave; v ukazni vrstici lahko določite seznam datotek, ki naj "
"se odprejo. Najprej se odpre prva navedena datoteka, nato pa ostale "
"datoteke. Vsaka datoteka bo odprta v novem oknu ali podoknu istega &kwave; "
"pojavka. Če določite nadomestne znake, lahko odprete veliko število datotek "
"hkrati."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:879
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For example, the following command starts a &kwave; and opens all sounds "
"provided by the freedesktop XDG sound theme, each in a new window or sub-"
"window:"
msgstr ""
"Naslednji ukaz na primer zažene &kwave; in odpre vse zvoke, ki jih ponuja "
"zvočna tema freedesktop XDG, vsakega v novem oknu ali podoknu:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:882
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<prompt>% </prompt><command>kwave <filename>/usr/share/sounds/freedesktop/"
"stereo/*.ogg</filename></command>"
msgstr ""
"<prompt>% </prompt><command>kwave <filename>/usr/share/sounds/freedesktop/"
"stereo/*.ogg</filename></command>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:884
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is also possible to pass &kwave; text commands, encoded as a special &URI;"
"<footnote><para>universal resource identifier</para></footnote>, this will "
"be described in a <link linkend=\"kwave_uri\">later section</link>."
msgstr ""
"Za &kwave; je možno je posredovati tudi besedilne ukaze, kodirane kot "
"poseben &URI;<footnote><para>univerzalni identifikator vira</para></"
"footnote>, in to bo opisano v <link linkend=\"kwave_uri\">poznejšem "
"razdelku</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:891
#, no-c-format
msgid "&GUI; Type"
msgstr "&GUI; Vrsta"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:892
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The parameter <literal>--gui=<replaceable>SDI</replaceable>|"
"<replaceable>MDI</replaceable>|<replaceable>TAB</replaceable></literal> lets "
"&kwave; start in one of the three possible &GUI; modes: <link linkend="
"\"gui_sdi\"><abbrev>SDI</abbrev></link>, <link linkend=\"gui_mdi"
"\"><abbrev>MDI</abbrev></link> or <link linkend=\"gui_tab\"><abbrev>TAB</"
"abbrev></link>."
msgstr ""
"Parameter <literal>--gui=<replaceable>SDI</replaceable>|<replaceable>MDI</"
"replaceable>|<replaceable>TAB</replaceable></literal> omogoča &kwave; da se "
"zažene v enem od treh možnih &GUI; načinov: <link linkend=\"gui_sdi"
"\"><abbrev>SDI</abbrev></link>, <link linkend=\"gui_mdi\"><abbrev>MDI</"
"abbrev></link> ali <link linkend=\"gui_tab\"><abbrev>TAB</abbrev></link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:901
#, no-c-format
msgid "Qt Toolkit options"
msgstr "Možnosti za Qt Toolkit"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:902
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In addition to a list of files, you can specify a list of <emphasis>Qt "
"toolkit</emphasis> options like <literal>-qwindowgeometry</literal> for "
"specifying the size and/or position of the first opened &kwave; window and/"
"or <literal>-display</literal> for starting the &kwave; on a different "
"display."
msgstr ""
"Poleg seznama datotek lahko določite seznam možnosti <emphasis>Zbira orodij "
"Qt</emphasis>, kot je <literal>-qwindowgeometry</literal> za določanje "
"velikosti in/ali položaja prvega odprtega okna &kwave; in/ali <literal>-"
"display</literal> za zagon &kwave; na drugem zaslonu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:909
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For example, the following command starts a &kwave; window with an initial "
"width of 600 pixels and a height of 400 pixels, with the right border "
"positioned 30 pixels away from the right and 0 pixels away from the top of "
"the screen."
msgstr ""
"Naslednji ukaz na primer zažene okno &kwave; z začetno širino 600 slikovnih "
"pik in višino 400 slikovnih pik, z desnim robom, ki je 30 slikovnih pik "
"stran od desne in 0 slikovnih pik stran od vrha zaslona."

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:914
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<prompt>% </prompt><command>kwave <parameter>--disable-splashscreen</"
"parameter> <parameter>-qwindowgeometry 600x400-30+0</parameter></command>"
msgstr ""
"<prompt>% </prompt><command>kwave <parameter>--disable-splashscreen</"
"parameter> <parameter>-qwindowgeometry 600x400-30+0</parameter></command>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:918
#, no-c-format
msgid "Startup Options"
msgstr "Možnosti zagona"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:919
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With the option <literal>--disable-splashscreen</literal> you can disable "
"the splash screen that comes up when starting &kwave;. This might be useful "
"when you start &kwave; from a script."
msgstr ""
"Z možnostjo <literal>--disable-splashscreen</literal> lahko onemogočite "
"začetni zaslon, ki se prikaže ob zagonu &kwave;. To je lahko koristno, ko "
"zaženete &kwave; iz skripta."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:925
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The command line option <literal>--iconic</literal> lets &kwave; start up "
"minimized (iconified). This might be useful when you want to start &kwave; "
"without &GUI; interaction, &eg; when running from a script. This option also "
"implicitly disables the splash screen!"
msgstr ""
"Možnost ukazne vrstice <literal>--iconic</literal> omogoča &kwave; "
"minimiziran (ikoniziran) zagon. To je lahko koristno, ko želite zagnati "
"&kwave; brez &GUI; interakcije, &eg;. pri izvajanju iz skripta. Ta možnost "
"tudi implicitno onemogoči začetni zaslon!"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:932
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By using the command line option <literal>--logfile=<replaceable>kwave.log</"
"replaceable></literal> you can log the sequence of actions of a &kwave; "
"session into a file. This is useful for debugging, you might be asked for "
"such a logfile when reporting an error."
msgstr ""
"Z uporabo možnosti ukazne vrstice <literal>--logfile=<replaceable>kwave.log</"
"replaceable></literal> lahko zabeležite zaporedje dejanj seje &kwave; v "
"datoteko. To je uporabno za odpravljanje napak, morda boste morali vnesti "
"takšno dnevniško datoteko, ko boste poročali o napaki."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:945
#, no-c-format
msgid "Opening and Saving files"
msgstr "Odpiranje in shranjevanje datotek"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:947
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Opening files with &kwave; works like in most other applications, you can"
msgstr ""
"Odpiranje datotek s &kwave; deluje kot v večini drugih aplikacij, lahko"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:951
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"specify a list of files on the <link linkend=\"command_line\">command line</"
"link> when starting &kwave;,"
msgstr ""
"določite seznam datotek v <link linkend=\"command_line\">ukazni vrstici</"
"link> ob zagonu &kwave;,"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:953
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"open an empty &kwave; window (for example with <menuchoice> "
"<shortcut><keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>W</keycap></keycombo></shortcut> "
"<guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>New...</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> ) and "
"put a file into it via <link linkend=\"drag_and_drop\">drag and drop</link>, "
"or you can"
msgstr ""
"odprete prazno okno &kwave; (na primer z <menuchoice> "
"<shortcut><keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>W</keycap></keycombo></shortcut> "
"<guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu><guimenuitem>Nova...</guimenuitem > </"
"menuchoice> ) in vanjo vstavite datoteko prek <link linkend=\"drag_and_drop"
"\">povleci in spusti</link> ali pa"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:961
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"open a file through the menu with <menuchoice> <shortcut><keycombo>&Ctrl;"
"<keycap>O</keycap></keycombo></shortcut> <guimenu>File</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Open</guimenuitem> </menuchoice>"
msgstr ""
"odprete datoteko v meniju z <menuchoice> <shortcut><keycombo>&Ctrl;"
"<keycap>O</keycap></keycombo></shortcut> <guimenu>Datoteka</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Odpri</guimenuitem> </menuchoice>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:967
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"or one of the last recently opened files under <menuchoice> <guimenu>File</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Open Recent</guimenuitem> </menuchoice>"
msgstr ""
"ali eno od zadnjih nedavno odprtih datotek pod <menuchoice> "
"<guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu><guimenuitem>Odpri nedavno</guimenuitem> </"
"menuchoice>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:973
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"save the current file with <menuchoice> <shortcut><keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>S</"
"keycap></keycombo></shortcut> <guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>Save</"
"guimenuitem> </menuchoice>,"
msgstr ""
"shranite trenutno datoteko s <menuchoice> <shortcut><keycombo>&Ctrl;"
"<keycap>S</keycap></keycombo></shortcut> <guimenu>Datoteka</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Shrani</guimenuitem> </menuchoice>,"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:980
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"save under a different name with <menuchoice> <shortcut><keycombo>&Shift;"
"&Ctrl;<keycap>S</keycap></keycombo></shortcut> <guimenu>File</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Save</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>As...</guimenuitem> </"
"menuchoice>"
msgstr ""
"shranite pod drugim imenom z <menuchoice> <shortcut><keycombo>&Shift;&Ctrl;"
"<keycap>S</keycap></keycombo></shortcut> <guimenu>Datoteka</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Shrani</guimenuitem ><guimenuitem>Kot...</guimenuitem> "
"</menuchoice>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:987
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"save all areas that are separated by markers, each one to an own file, with "
"<menuchoice> <guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>Save</"
"guimenuitem><guimenuitem>Blocks...</guimenuitem> </menuchoice>"
msgstr ""
"shranite vsa področja, ki so ločena z oznakami, vsako v lastno datoteko, z "
"<menuchoice> <guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu><guimenuitem>Shrani</"
"guimenuitem><guimenuitem>Bloki ...</guimenuitem> </menuchoice >"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:994
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"or only the current selection with <menuchoice> <guimenu>File</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Save</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>Selection...</"
"guimenuitem> </menuchoice>"
msgstr ""
"ali samo trenutni izbor z <menuchoice> <guimenu>Datoteka</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Shrani</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>Izbor...</guimenuitem> "
"</menuchoice>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1003
#, no-c-format
msgid "Supported File formats"
msgstr "Podprti formati datotek"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1005
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kwave; supports the following file formats:"
msgstr "&kwave; podpira naslednje formate datotek:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1011
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The favourite file format of &kwave; is (like you can guess from the name) "
"<filename>.wav</filename>. This format is very common to other \"operating "
"systems\" and also is commonly used within the &plasma; environment."
msgstr ""
"Najljubši format datoteke &kwave; je (kot lahko uganete iz imena) <filename>."
"wav</filename>. Ta oblika je zelo pogosta pri drugih \"operacijskih sistemih"
"\" in se pogosto uporablja tudi v &plasma; okolju."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1016
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The second format that &kwave; supports is \"ASCII\". You can export to and "
"also import from ASCII. Please be aware that storing in this format might "
"produce very large files! The file format will be described <link linkend="
"\"ascii_format\">below</link>."
msgstr ""
"Drugi format, ki ga &kwave; podpira, je \"ASCII\". Izvažate lahko v in tudi "
"uvažate iz ASCII. Upoštevajte, da lahko shranjevanje v tej obliki ustvari "
"zelo velike datoteke! Format datoteke bo opisan <link linkend=\"ascii_format"
"\">spodaj</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1022
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<filename>.mp3</filename> and <filename>.mp2</filename> import is available "
"through <ulink url=\"&url_libmad;\">libmad</ulink> for the MP3 decoding in "
"combination with <ulink url=\"&url_id3lib;\">id3lib</ulink> for decoding ID3 "
"tags and <ulink url=\"&url_lame;\">lame</ulink> for encoding."
msgstr ""
"Uvoz <filename>.mp3</filename> in <filename>.mp2</filename> je na voljo prek "
"<ulink url=\"&url_libmad;\">libmad</ulink> za dekodiranje MP3 v kombinaciji "
"z <ulink url=\"&url_id3lib;\">id3lib</ulink> za dekodiranje oznak ID3 in "
"<ulink url=\"&url_lame;\">lame</ulink> za kodiranje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1031
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Ogg/Vorbis (<filename>*.ogg</filename>) import and export. See <ulink url="
"\"&url_ogg_vorbis;\">&url_ogg_vorbis;</ulink> for details."
msgstr ""
"Uvoz in izvoz Ogg/Vorbis (<filename>*.ogg</filename>). Za podrobnosti glejte "
"<ulink url=\"&url_ogg_vorbis;\">&url_ogg_vorbis;</ulink>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1035
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"FLAC (<filename>*.flac</filename>) import and export. See <ulink url="
"\"&url_flac;\">&url_flac;</ulink> for details."
msgstr ""
"Uvoz in izvoz FLAC (<filename>*.flac</filename>). Za podrobnosti glejte "
"<ulink url=\"&url_flac;\">&url_flac;</ulink>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1040
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Additionally you can import file formats like <filename>*.8svx</filename> "
"(Amiga IFF/8SVX Sound File Format), <filename>*.au</filename> (NeXT, Sun "
"Audio), <filename>*.aiff</filename> (Audio Interchange Format), <filename>*."
"avr</filename> (Audio Visual Research File Format), <filename>*.caf</"
"filename> (Core Audio Format), <filename>*.nist</filename> (NIST SPHERE "
"Audio File Format), <filename>*.sf</filename> (Berkeley, IRCAM, Carl Sound "
"Format), <filename>*.smp</filename> (Sample Vision Format), <filename>*.snd</"
"filename> (NeXT, Sun Audio), <filename>*.voc</filename> (Creative Voice) and "
"others through the <ulink url=\"&url_libaudiofile;\">audiofile</ulink> "
"plugin."
msgstr ""
"Poleg tega lahko uvozite oblike datotek, kot so <filename>*.8svx</filename> "
"(Amiga IFF/8SVX Sound File Format), <filename>*.au</filename> (NeXT, Sun "
"Audio), <filename>*.aiff </filename> (Audio Interchange Format), <filename>*."
"avr</filename> (Audio Visual Research File Format), <filename>*.caf</"
"filename> (Core Audio Format), <filename>*.nist </filename> (NIST SPHERE "
"Audio File Format), <filename>*.sf</filename> (Berkeley, IRCAM, Carl Sound "
"Format), <filename>*.smp</filename> (Sample Vision Format), <filename >*."
"snd</filename> (NeXT, Sun Audio), <filename>*.voc</filename> (Creative "
"Voice) in drugi prek vtičnika <ulink url=\"&url_libaudiofile;\">avdiofile</"
"ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1063
#, no-c-format
msgid "Converting to and from .wav"
msgstr "Pretvarjanje v .wav in iz njega"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1065
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The best way to work with formats other than those supported by &kwave; is "
"to use an external converter program. A good set of tools for this is in the "
"<ulink url=\"&url_sox;\">SoX</ulink> package, they have also some nice "
"documentation!"
msgstr ""
"Najboljši način za delo z oblikami, ki niso tiste, ki jih podpira &kwave; je "
"uporaba zunanjega programa za pretvorbo. Dober nabor orodij za to je v "
"paketu <ulink url=\"&url_sox;\">SoX</ulink>, imajo tudi nekaj lepe "
"dokumentacije!"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1073
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The plans for future include support for import and also export filters for "
"more formats and maybe some filter that uses a user-definable script with a "
"call to an external filter, so that even formats not supported by "
"<literal>SoX</literal> can be read and/or written."
msgstr ""
"Načrti za prihodnost vključujejo podporo za uvozne in tudi izvozne filtre za "
"več formatov in morda kakšen filter, ki uporablja uporabniško definiran "
"skript s klicem zunanjega filtra, tako da lahko beremo in zapisujemo tudi "
"formate, ki jih <literal>SoX</literal> ne podpira."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1081
#, no-c-format
msgid "Format of ASCII files"
msgstr "Format datotek ASCII"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1082
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The ASCII format is quite useful for scientific and educational purposes. "
"Due to its simple format, you can either write simple files on your own with "
"a text editor or you can use the output of some other application and "
"convert it into ASCII. As the format is <emphasis>really</emphasis> simple, "
"you should not have big problems in writing a converter and most scientific "
"applications use to have some kind of their own ASCII format for export."
msgstr ""
"Format ASCII je zelo uporaben za znanstvene in izobraževalne namene. Zaradi "
"preprostega formata lahko preproste datoteke pišete sami z urejevalnikom "
"besedil ali pa uporabite izpis kakšne druge aplikacije in ga pretvorite v "
"ASCII. Ker je format <emphasis>zares</emphasis> preprost, ne bi smeli imeti "
"večjih težav pri pisanju pretvornika in večina znanstvenih aplikacij "
"uporablja nekakšen lasten format ASCII za izvoz."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1094
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The format of an ASCII file is quite simple and has the following rules:"
msgstr "Format datoteke ASCII je precej preprost in ima naslednja pravila:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1097
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"At the start of the file comes a block of properties, with one property per "
"line."
msgstr "Na začetku datoteke je blok lastnosti, z eno lastnostjo na vrstico."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1101
#, no-c-format
msgid "Each property line starts with <literal>##</literal>."
msgstr "Vsaka vrstica lastnosti se začne z <literal>##</literal>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1104
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After the properties comes a list of samples, with one sample per line. When "
"using multiple channels, the samples are separated by commas."
msgstr ""
"Za lastnostmi sledi seznam vzorcev z enim vzorcem na vrstico. Pri uporabi "
"več kanalov so vzorci ločeni z vejicami."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1108
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Lines might end with a carriage return and/or a line feed character (so DOS "
"files are supported too). But when saving, files will always be saved with "
"line feed character as the end of the line."
msgstr ""
"Vrstice se lahko končajo z znakom carriage return in/ali znakom za line "
"feed(zato so podprte tudi datoteke DOS). Toda pri shranjevanju bodo datoteke "
"vedno shranjene z znakom za line feed na koncu vrstice."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1114
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Empty lines and characters after a <literal>#</literal> are treated as "
"comments and are ignored."
msgstr ""
"Prazne vrstice in znaki za <literal>#</literal> se obravnavajo kot "
"komentarji in se prezrejo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1118
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Values have to be given in signed integer format with a 24 bit range, which "
"is the internal storage format of &kwave;."
msgstr ""
"Vrednosti morajo biti podane v formatu celega števila s predznakom s 24-"
"bitnim obsegom, kar je notranji format za shranjevanje &kwave;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1122
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Everything after a <literal>#</literal> (except property lines, see above) "
"will be treated as comment and will be ignored. Empty lines will also be "
"ignored."
msgstr ""
"Vse za <literal>#</literal> (razen vrstic lastnosti, glejte zgoraj) bo "
"obravnavano kot komentar in bo prezrto. Prav tako bodo prezrte prazne "
"vrstice."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1130
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here is an example of a simple ASCII file that represents a sine wave with "
"eleven samples:"
msgstr ""
"Tukaj je primer preproste datoteke ASCII, ki predstavlja sinusni val z "
"enajstimi vzorci:"

