#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:5229
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_export_k3b; (Export to K3b Project)"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_export_k3b; (Izvoz v projekt K3b)"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:5237
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the K3b Export Plugin"
msgstr "Posnetek zaslona izvoznega vtičnika K3b"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:5244
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_export_k3b;"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_export_k3b;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5253
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Saves all sections between markers into a separate file and creates a K3b "
"project file. After having successfully written all files it is possible to "
"start <ulink url=\"&url_k3b;\">K3b</ulink> and burn the result to an audio "
"&CD;. This is useful for splitting a file with a recording that consists of "
"several parts, which are separated by labels, and then burn it to an audio "
"&CD; with multiple tracks, including &CD; text meta data which is extracted "
"from the descriptions of the labels."
msgstr ""
"Shrani vse razdelke med označevalci v ločeno datoteko in ustvari projektno "
"datoteko K3b. Ko uspešno zapišete vse datoteke, lahko zaženete <ulink url="
"\"&url_k3b;\">K3b</ulink> in rezultat zapišete na zvočni &CD;. To je "
"uporabno za razdelitev datoteke s posnetkom, ki je sestavljen iz več delov, "
"ki so ločeni z oznakami, in nato zapis na zvočni &CD; z več skladbami, "
"vključno z &CD; besedilni meta podatki, ki so izvlečeni iz opisov oznak."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5263
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"(This plugin is internally using the <link linkend=\"plugin_sect_saveblocks"
"\" endterm=\"plugin_title_saveblocks\"></link> plugin.)"
msgstr ""
"(Ta vtičnik interno uporablja vtičnik <link linkend=\"plugin_sect_saveblocks"
"\" endterm=\"plugin_title_saveblocks\"></link>.)"

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:5275 index.docbook:6503
#, no-c-format
msgid "pattern"
msgstr "vzorec"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5277
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A pattern that will be used for detecting title and artist from the label at "
"the start of a section. It supports the following wildcards which will be "
"replaced by the corresponding content when creating the &CD; text meta data:"
msgstr ""
"Vzorec, ki bo uporabljen za zaznavanje naslova in izvajalca iz oznake na "
"začetku odseka. Podpira naslednje nadomestne znake, ki bodo nadomeščeni z "
"ustrezno vsebino pri ustvarjanju &CD; besedilni meta podatki:"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5289 index.docbook:6516
#, no-c-format
msgid "wildcard"
msgstr "nadomestni znak"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5295
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;<command>[%artist]</command>"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;<command>[%artist]</command>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5296
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Will be replaced with the artist that performed the corresponding block or "
"alternatively the author."
msgstr "Nadomestil ga bo izvajalec, ki je izvedel ustrezen blok, ali pa avtor."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5302 index.docbook:6559
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;<command>[%title]</command>"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;<command>[%title]</command>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5303 index.docbook:6560
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Will be replaced with the title of the block, which is taken from the "
"descriptive text of the label at the <emphasis>start</emphasis> of the "
"block. If that text is empty it will fall back to the title of the file (see "
"file information item \"<link linkend=\"INF_NAME\">Name</link>\"). If this "
"also does not exist, it will fall back to the base file name as described "
"above."
msgstr ""
"Nadomeščen bo z naslovom bloka, ki je vzet iz opisnega besedila oznake na "
"<emphasis>začetku</emphasis> bloka. Če je to besedilo prazno, se vrne k "
"naslovu datoteke (glejte postavko informacij o datoteki »<link linkend="
"\"INF_NAME\">Ime</link>«). Če tudi ta ne obstaja, se bo vrnila na osnovno "
"ime datoteke, kot je opisano zgoraj."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5317
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Example: <quote><command><literal>[%title] ([%artist])</literal></command></"
"quote> will detect author <quote><command><literal>Beethoven</literal></"
"command></quote> and title <quote><command><literal>Symphony No. 5</"
"literal></command></quote> from the string <quote><command><literal>Symphony "
"No. 5 (Beethoven)</literal></command></quote>."
msgstr ""
"Primer: <quote><command><literal>[%title] ([%artist])</literal></command></"
"quote> bo zaznal avtorja <quote><command><literal>Beethoven</literal> </"
"command></quote> in naslov <quote><command><literal>Simfonija št. 5</"
"literal></command></quote> iz niza <quote><command><literal>Simfonija št. 5 "
"(Beethoven)</literal></command></quote>."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:5327 index.docbook:6644
#, no-c-format
msgid "selection only"
msgstr "samo izbor"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5334 index.docbook:5388 index.docbook:5509 index.docbook:5601
#: index.docbook:5800 index.docbook:6028 index.docbook:6348 index.docbook:6597
#: index.docbook:6651 index.docbook:6729 index.docbook:6865 index.docbook:7062
#: index.docbook:7129
#, no-c-format
msgid "value"
msgstr "vrednost"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5340 index.docbook:5394 index.docbook:5515 index.docbook:5607
#: index.docbook:5806 index.docbook:6034 index.docbook:6603 index.docbook:6657
#: index.docbook:6735 index.docbook:7068 index.docbook:7135
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;<command>0</command>"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;<command>0</command>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5341 index.docbook:6658
#, no-c-format
msgid "Save all sections of the whole file."
msgstr "Shranite vse razdelke celotne datoteke."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5346 index.docbook:5401 index.docbook:5519 index.docbook:5611
#: index.docbook:5813 index.docbook:6041 index.docbook:6611 index.docbook:6663
#: index.docbook:6739 index.docbook:7072 index.docbook:7076 index.docbook:7139
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;<command>1</command>"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;<command>1</command>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5347 index.docbook:6664
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Save only the sections that are within the current selection. If nothing is "
"selected, the whole file will be saved."
msgstr ""
"Shranite samo razdelke, ki so znotraj trenutnega izbora. Če ne izberete "
"ničesar, bo shranjena celotna datoteka."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:5361
#, no-c-format
msgid "project file"
msgstr "projektna datoteka"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5363
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The name of the K3b project file, which will also be used as the base name "
"for the exported file names."
msgstr ""
"Ime projektne datoteke K3b bo uporabljeno kot osnovno ime za imena izvoženih "
"datotek."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:5371 index.docbook:6635
#, no-c-format
msgid "export location"
msgstr "lokacija izvoza"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5373
#, no-c-format
msgid "The location where the blocks should be saved."
msgstr "Lokacija kamor naj bi bili shranjeni bloki."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:5380
#, no-c-format
msgid "overwrite policy"
msgstr "pravilnik o prepisovanju"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5382 index.docbook:6591
#, no-c-format
msgid "Determines where the numbering should start."
msgstr "Določa, kje naj se oštevilčenje začne."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5395 index.docbook:6612
#, no-c-format
msgid "Always start with index 1, with the risk of overwriting existing files."
msgstr ""
"Vedno začnite z indeksom 1, s tveganjem prepisovanja obstoječih datotek."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5402 index.docbook:6604
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Continue after the index of the highest index that already exists, this "
"avoids overwriting existing files."
msgstr ""
"Nadaljujte po indeksu najvišjega indeksa, ki že obstaja, s tem se izognete "
"prepisovanju obstoječih datotek."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:5422
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_fileinfo; (File Info)"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_fileinfo; (Informacije o datoteki)"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:5430
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the File Info Plugin"
msgstr "Posnetek zaslona vtičnika z informacijami o datoteki"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:5437
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_fileinfo;"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_fileinfo;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5446
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Provides a dialog window to view and change parameters and meta data of the "
"currently opened file. See section <link linkend=\"fileinfo\" endterm="
"\"title_fileinfo\"></link> in this manual."
msgstr ""
"Nudi pogovorno okno za ogled in spreminjanje parametrov in metapodatkov "
"trenutno odprte datoteke. Glejte razdelek <link linkend=\"fileinfo\" endterm="
"\"title_fileinfo\"></link> v tem priročniku."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:5458
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_goto; (Goto Position)"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_goto; (Goto Position - Pojdi na pozicijo)"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:5466
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the Goto Position Plugin"
msgstr "Posnetek zaslona vtičnika Goto Position"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:5473
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_goto;"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_goto;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5482
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Shows a dialog with the possibility to set the current position of the "
"selection to a new value, either by a time in milliseconds, by a position in "
"samples or by percentage of the length of the current file."
msgstr ""
"Prikaže pogovorno okno z možnostjo nastavitve trenutnega položaja izbora na "
"novo vrednost, bodisi glede na čas v milisekundah, položaj v vzorcih ali "
"odstotek dolžine trenutne datoteke."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:5503 index.docbook:5595 index.docbook:5794 index.docbook:6022
#: index.docbook:7055
#, no-c-format
msgid "mode"
msgstr "način"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5516 index.docbook:5608
#, no-c-format
msgid "position is given in milliseconds"
msgstr "pozicija je podana v milisekundah"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5520 index.docbook:5612
#, no-c-format
msgid "position is given in samples"
msgstr "pozicija je podana v vzorcih"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5523 index.docbook:5615 index.docbook:6743 index.docbook:7143
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;<command>2</command>"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;<command>2</command>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5524 index.docbook:5616
#, no-c-format
msgid "position is given in percentage of the file length"
msgstr "pozicija je podana v odstotkih dolžine datoteke"

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:5532 index.docbook:5624
#, no-c-format
msgid "position"
msgstr "pozicija"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5534
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"position to go to, in milliseconds, samples or percentage of the length of "
"the file, depending on the parameter <parameter>mode</parameter>."
msgstr ""
"pozicija do katerega želite iti, v milisekundah, vzorcih ali odstotkih "
"dolžine datoteke, odvisno od parametra <parameter>mode</parameter>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:5548
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_insert_at; (Insert At)"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_insert_at; (Insert At - Vstavi pri)"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:5556
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the Insert At Plugin"
msgstr "Posnetek zaslona vtičnika Insert At"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:5563
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_insert_at;"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_insert_at;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5572
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Similar to the <link linkend=\"plugin_sect_goto\" endterm=\"plugin_title_goto"
"\"></link> plugin, but shows a dialog with the possibility to insert the "
"current content of the clipboard at a given position, either by a time in "
"milliseconds, by a position in samples or by percentage of the length of the "
"current file."
msgstr ""
"Podobno kot vtičnik <link linkend=\"plugin_sect_goto\" endterm="
"\"plugin_title_goto\"></link>, vendar prikazuje pogovorno okno z možnostjo "
"vstavljanja trenutne vsebine odložišča na določeno mesto bodisi za čas v "
"milisekundah, tako položaj v vzorcih ali odstotek dolžine trenutne datoteke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5626
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"position where to insert the clipboard data, in milliseconds, samples or "
"percentage of the length of the file, depending on the parameter "
"<parameter>mode</parameter>."
msgstr ""
"položaj, kamor želite vstaviti podatke iz odložišča, v milisekundah, vzorcih "
"ali odstotkih dolžine datoteke, odvisno od parametra <parameter>mode</"
"parameter>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:5641
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_lowpass; (Low Pass Filter)"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_lowpass; (Low Pass Filter - nizkoprepustni filter)"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:5649
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the Low Pass Filter Plugin"
msgstr "Posnetek zaslona vtičnika Low Pass Filter"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:5656
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_lowpass;"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_lowpass;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5665
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Applies a simple low pass filter to the current selection. A low pass filter "
"lets frequencies below a <emphasis>border frequency</emphasis> pass and "
"filters out frequencies that are above the border frequency."
msgstr ""
"Uporabi preprost nizkopasovni filter za trenutno izbiro. Nizkoprepustni "
"filter prepušča frekvence pod <emphasis>mejno frekvenco</emphasis> in "
"filtrira frekvence, ki so nad mejno frekvenco."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5670
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The filter has grade two and is implemented as described in the book "
"<citetitle>\"The manifold joys of conformal mapping, applications to digital "
"filtering in the studio</citetitle> by <author> <personname> "
"<firstname>James A.</firstname> <surname>Moorer</surname> </personname> </"
"author> (JAES, Vol. 31, No. 11, 1983 November)."
msgstr ""
"Filter ima drugo stopnjo in je implementiran, kot je opisano v knjigi "
"<citetitle>»The manifold joys of conformal mapping, applications to digital "
"filtering in the studio</citetitle> avtorja <author> <personname> "
"<firstname>James A.</firstname> <surname>Moorer</surname> </personname> </"
"author> (JAES, letnik 31, št. 11, november 1983)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5691
#, no-c-format
msgid "The border frequency of the low pass filter in Hz."
msgstr "Mejna frekvenca nizkopasovnega filtra v Hz."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:5704
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_newsignal; (New Signal)"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_newsignal; (Novi signal)"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:5712
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the New Signal Plugin"
msgstr "Posnetek zaslona vtičnika New Signal"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:5719
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_newsignal;"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_newsignal;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5728
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Provides a dialog to create a new file. Please refer to the section <link "
"linkend=\"newsignal\" endterm=\"sect_title_newsignal\"></link> in this "
"manual for more information."
msgstr ""
"Ponuja pogovorno okno za ustvarjanje nove datoteke. Za več informacij glejte "
"razdelek <link linkend=\"newsignal\" endterm=\"sect_title_newsignal\"></"
"link> v tem priročniku."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5739
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<link linkend=\"cmd_sect_newsignal\" endterm=\"cmd_title_newsignal\"></link>,"
msgstr ""
"<link linkend=\"cmd_sect_newsignal\" endterm=\"cmd_title_newsignal\"></link>,"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:5748
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_noise; (Noise Generator)"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_noise; (Noise Generator - Generator šuma)"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:5756
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the Noise Generator Plugin"
msgstr "Posnetek zaslona vtičnika Noise Generator"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:5763
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_noise;"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_noise;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5772
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Adds some amount of white noise to the current selection. The amount of "
"noise can be selected between zero (no noise, original remains unchanged) "
"and one (original will be replaced by 100% noise)."
msgstr ""
"Trenutnemu izboru doda nekaj belega šuma. Količina šuma je lahko izbrana med "
"nič (brez šuma, original ostane nespremenjen) in ena (original bo zamenjan s "
"100-odstotnim šumom)."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:5785
#, no-c-format
msgid "level"
msgstr "raven"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5787
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Noise level, always has to be a floating point number above zero and below "
"or equal to one."
msgstr ""
"Raven šuma mora biti vedno število s plavajočo vejico nad nič in pod ali "
"enako ena."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5807
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enter the noise value as percentage of the amplitude, from 0 to 100."
msgstr "Vnesite vrednost šuma kot odstotek amplitude od 0 do 100."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5814
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enter the noise in decibel, from -21 dB to 0 dB."
msgstr "Vnesite šum v decibelih, od -21 dB do 0 dB."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:5831
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_normalize; (Normalizer)"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_normalize; (Normalizer - Normalizator)"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:5835
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_normalize;"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_normalize;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5844
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Normalizes the volume level of the current selection. Use this if the volume "
"of your signal is too low or too high."
msgstr ""
"Normalizira raven glasnosti trenutne izbire. To uporabite, če je glasnost "
"vašega signala prenizka ali previsoka."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5848
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The algorithm is taken from the <citetitle>normalize</citetitle> project, "
"and was originally written by <link linkend=\"author_Chris_Vaill\"> <author> "
"<personname> <firstname>Chris</firstname> <surname>Vaill</surname> </"
"personname> </author> </link>."
msgstr ""
"Algoritem je vzet iz projekta <citetitle>normalize</citetitle> in ga je "
"prvotno napisal <link linkend=\"author_Chris_Vaill\"> <author> <personname> "
"<firstname>Chris</firstname> <surname>Vaill</surname > </personname> </"
"author> </link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:5866
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_notch_filter; (Notch Filter)"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_notch_filter; (Notch Filter - Zarezni filter)"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:5874
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the Notch Filter Plugin"
msgstr "Posnetek zaslona vtičnika Notch Filter"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:5881
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_notch_filter;"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_notch_filter;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5890
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Applies a notch filter to the current selection. A notch filter removes a "
"small range of frequencies around a <emphasis>center frequency</emphasis> "
"and lets all other frequencies below and above the center frequency by more "
"than half of the <emphasis>bandwidth</emphasis> pass."
msgstr ""
"Uporabi zarezni filter za trenutni izbor. Zarezni filter odstrani majhen "
"razpon frekvenc okoli <emphasis>centralne frekvence</emphasis> in prepusti "
"vse druge frekvence pod in nad sredinsko frekvenco za več kot polovico "
"<emphasis>pasovne širine</emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5897
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use this to filter out single distortion frequencies."
msgstr "Uporabite to za filtriranje posameznih frekvenc popačenja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5900
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The filter has grade two and is based on the implementation of <link linkend="
"\"author_Juhana_Sadeharju\"> <author> <personname> <firstname>Juhana</"
"firstname> <surname>Sadeharju</surname> </personname> </author> </link>."
msgstr ""
"Filter ima drugo stopnjo in temelji na implementaciji <link linkend="
"\"author_Juhana_Sadeharju\"> <author> <personname> <firstname>Juhana</"
"firstname> <surname>Sadeharju</surname> </personname> </author> </link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:5941
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_pitch_shift; (Pitch Shift)"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_pitch_shift; (Pitch Shift - Pomik višine)"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:5949
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the Pitch Shift Plugin"
msgstr "Posnetek zaslona vtičnika Pitch Shift"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:5956
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_pitch_shift;"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_pitch_shift;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5965
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The pitch shift effect modifies the signal by changing the speed of the "
"content, but with keeping the original length. You can select the relative "
"speed either by factor from 1/10 to x5, or as a percentage from 1% to 400% "
"of the original speed."
msgstr ""
"Učinek premika višine spremeni signal tako, da spremeni višino vsebine, "
"vendar ohrani prvotno dolžino. Relativno višino lahko izberete s faktorjem "
"od 1/10 do x5 ali kot odstotek od 1 % do 400 % prvotne višine."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5971
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A speed factor below 1.0 pitches the signal down (lower voice, makes voices "
"sound older), factor 1.0 does no change and a factor above 1.0 pitches the "
"signal up (higher voice, Mickey Mouse effect)."
msgstr ""
"Faktor višine pod 1,0 zniža signal (nižji glas, zaradi česar glasovi zvenijo "
"starejši), faktor 1,0 se ne spremeni, faktor nad 1,0 pa dvigne signal (višji "
"glas, učinek Mikija Miške)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5977
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The implementation is based on the work of <link linkend="
"\"author_Jeff_Tranter\"> <author> <personname> <firstname>Jeff</firstname> "
"<surname>Tranter</surname> </personname> </author> </link> and <link linkend="
"\"author_Stefan_Westerfeld\"> <author> <personname> <firstname>Stefan</"
"firstname> <surname>Westerfeld</surname> </personname> </author> </link>"
msgstr ""
"Izvedba temelji na delih <link linkend=\"author_Jeff_Tranter\"> <author> "
"<personname> <firstname>Jeff</firstname> <surname>Tranter</surname> </"
"personname> </author> </link> in <link linkend=\"author_Stefan_Westerfeld\"> "
"<author> <personname> <firstname>Stefan</firstname> <surname>Westerfeld</"
"surname> </personname> </author> </link>"

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6004
#, no-c-format
msgid "speed"
msgstr "višina"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6006
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Factor for changing the speed, has to be a floating point number between "
"0.001 and 4.0."
msgstr ""
"Faktor za spreminjanje višine mora biti število s plavajočo vejico med 0,001 "
"in 4,0."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6015
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Frequency internally used by the filter in Hz, has to be between 2.0 and "
"10.0."
msgstr ""
"Frekvenca, ki jo interno uporablja filter v Hz, mora biti med 2,0 in 10,0."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:6035
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enter the speed value as factor from 1/10 to x5."
msgstr "Vnesite vrednost višine kot faktor od 1/10 do x5."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:6042
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enter the speed value as percentage from 1 to 400."
msgstr "Vnesite vrednost višine v odstotkih od 1 do 400."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6059
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_playback; (Playback)"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_playback; (Playback - Predvajanje v ozadju)"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:6067
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the Playback Plugin"
msgstr "Posnetek zaslona vtičnika za Playback"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:6074
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_playback;"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_playback;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6083
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Provides a dialog to set up the playback parameters. Please refer to the "
"section <link linkend=\"playback\" endterm=\"sect_title_playback\"></link> "
"in this manual for more information."
msgstr ""
"Nudi pogovorno okno za nastavitev parametrov predvajanja v ozadju. Za več "
"informacij glejte razdelek <link linkend=\"playback\" endterm="
"\"sect_title_playback\"></link> v tem priročniku."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6096
#, no-c-format
msgid "playback method"
msgstr "način predvajanja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6098
#, no-c-format
msgid "The method used for playback, see <filename>PlayBackParam.h</filename>."
msgstr ""
"Način, uporabljen za predvajanje, glejte <filename>PlayBackParam.h</"
"filename>."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6105
#, no-c-format
msgid "playback device"
msgstr "naprava za predvajanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6107
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A string that determines the playback device or channel. The meaning depends "
"on the playback method."
msgstr ""
"Niz, ki določa predvajalno napravo ali kanal. Pomen je odvisen od načina "
"predvajanja."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6115 index.docbook:6270
#, no-c-format
msgid "channels"
msgstr "kanali"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6117
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The number of channels to use for playback, currently supports only 1 (mono) "
"or 2 (stereo)."
msgstr ""
"Število kanalov, ki se uporabljajo za predvajanje, trenutno podpira samo 1 "
"(mono) ali 2 (stereo)."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6124 index.docbook:6304
#, no-c-format
msgid "bits per sample"
msgstr "bitov na vzorec"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6126
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The number of bits per sample for playback, should be 8, 16, 24 or 32. "
"Depends on the playback method and the playback device."
msgstr ""
"Število bitov na vzorec za predvajanje mora biti 8, 16, 24 ali 32. Odvisno "
"od načina predvajanja in naprave za predvajanje."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6135 index.docbook:6321
#, no-c-format
msgid "buffer size"
msgstr "velikost medpomnilnika"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6137
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Determines the size of the playback buffer, used as exponent for calculating "
"the real buffer size as 2^n, &eg; setting this to 16 gives a buffer size of "
"2^16 = 64 kB."
msgstr ""
"Določa velikost medpomnilnika za predvajanje, ki se uporablja kot eksponent "
"za izračun dejanske velikosti medpomnilnika kot 2^n, &eg; nastavitev tega na "
"16 daje velikost medpomnilnika 2^16 = 64 kB."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6152
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_record; (Record)"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_record; (Record - Snemaj)"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:6160
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the Record Plugin"
msgstr "Posnetek zaslona vtičnika Record"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:6167
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_record;"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_record;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6176
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Provides a dialog to set up the record parameters and to do a recording. "
"Please refer to the section <link linkend=\"recording\" endterm="
"\"sect_title_recording\"></link> in this manual for more information."
msgstr ""
"Nudi pogovorno okno za nastavitev parametrov zapisa in snemanja Za več "
"informacij glejte razdelek <link linkend=\"recording\" endterm="
"\"sect_title_recording\"></link> v tem priročniku."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6189
#, no-c-format
msgid "recording method"
msgstr "način snemanja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6191
#, no-c-format
msgid "The method used for recording, see <filename>RecordParams.h</filename>."
msgstr ""
"Metoda, uporabljena za snemanje, glejte <filename>RecordParams.h</filename>."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6198
#, no-c-format
msgid "pre recording enabled"
msgstr "predhodno snemanje omogočeno"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6200
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enable/disable pre recording (1 if enabled, 0 if disabled)."
msgstr ""
"Omogoči/onemogoči predhodno snemanje (1, če je omogočeno, 0, če je "
"onemogočeno)."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6206
#, no-c-format
msgid "pre recording time"
msgstr "čas pred snemanjem"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6208
#, no-c-format
msgid "Number of seconds for pre recording."
msgstr "Število sekund za predhodno snemanje."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6214
#, no-c-format
msgid "limit recording time"
msgstr "omejite čas snemanja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6216
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enable/disable limiting of recording time (1 if limited, 0 if not limited)."
msgstr ""
"Omogoči/onemogoči omejevanje časa snemanja (1, če je omejen, 0, če ni "
"omejen)."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6222
#, no-c-format
msgid "recording time"
msgstr "čas snemanja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6224
#, no-c-format
msgid "Duration of the recording in seconds."
msgstr "Trajanje snemanja v sekundah."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6230
#, no-c-format
msgid "use starting time"
msgstr "uporabite začetni čas"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6232
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enable/disable starting time (1 if used, 0 if not used)."
msgstr ""
"Omogoči/onemogoči začetni čas (1, če je uporabljen, 0, če ni uporabljen)."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6238
#, no-c-format
msgid "starting time"
msgstr "začetni čas"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6240
#, no-c-format
msgid "Date/time to start the recording, in ISO format."
msgstr "Datum/čas začetka snemanja v formatu ISO."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6246
#, no-c-format
msgid "use trigger level"
msgstr "uporabite sprožilni nivo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6248
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enable/disable trigger level (1 if used, 0 if not used)."
msgstr ""
"Omogoči/onemogoči raven sprožitve (1, če se uporablja, 0, če se ne "
"uporablja)."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6254
#, no-c-format
msgid "trigger level"
msgstr "nivo sprožitve"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6256
#, no-c-format
msgid "Trigger level in percent."
msgstr "Stopnja sprožitve v odstotkih."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6262
#, no-c-format
msgid "recording device"
msgstr "snemalna naprava"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6264
#, no-c-format
msgid "A string that determines the recording device."
msgstr "Niz, ki določa snemalno napravo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6272
#, no-c-format
msgid "The number of channels to use for recording."
msgstr "Število kanalov, ki se uporabljajo za snemanje."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6278
#, no-c-format
msgid "sample rate"
msgstr "hitrost vzorčenja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6280
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>Sample rate in samples per second.</para>"
msgstr "<para>Hitrost vzorčenja v vzorcih na sekundo.</para>"

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6286
#, no-c-format
msgid "compression"
msgstr "stiskanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6288
#, no-c-format
msgid "Compression to use for storing the samples."
msgstr "Stiskanje, ki se uporablja za shranjevanje vzorcev."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6294
#, no-c-format
msgid "sample format"
msgstr "vzorčni format"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6296
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sample format to use for storing the samples, see <link linkend=\"sample-"
"formats\">section about sample formats</link>."
msgstr ""
"Vzorčni format, ki ga želite uporabiti za shranjevanje vzorcev, glejte <link "
"linkend=\"sample-formats\">razdelek o vzorčnih formatih</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6306
#, no-c-format
msgid "The number of bits per sample for recording, should be 8, 16, 24 or 32."
msgstr "Število bitov na vzorec za snemanje mora biti 8, 16, 24 ali 32."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6313
#, no-c-format
msgid "buffer count"
msgstr "število medpomnilnikov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6315
#, no-c-format
msgid "Determines the number buffers used for recording."
msgstr "Določa število medpomnilnikov, ki se uporabljajo za snemanje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6323
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Determines the size of the recording buffer, used as exponent for "
"calculating the real buffer size as 2^n, &eg; setting this to 16 gives a "
"buffer size of 2^16 = 64 kB."
msgstr ""
"Določa velikost medpomnilnika za snemanje, ki se uporablja kot eksponent za "
"izračun dejanske velikosti medpomnilnika kot 2^n, &eg;. nastavitev tega na "
"16 daje velikost medpomnilnika 2^16 = 64 kB."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:6335
#, no-c-format
msgid "Alternative Parameters:"
msgstr "Alternativni parametri:"

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6339
#, no-c-format
msgid "record plugin direct mode"
msgstr "neposredni način snemanja vtičnika"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6341
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Can be used as a single parameter for setting up the plugin. The following "
"values are possible:"
msgstr ""
"Lahko se uporablja kot en sam parameter za nastavitev vtičnika. Možne so "
"naslednje vrednosti:"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:6354
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;<command>format</command>"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;<command>format</command>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:6355
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Open the recording dialog and select the <guilabel>Format</guilabel> tab."
msgstr ""
"Odprite pogovorno okno za snemanje in izberite zavihek <guilabel>Oblika</"
"guilabel>."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:6360
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;<command>source</command>"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;<command>source</command>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:6361
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Open the recording dialog and select the <guilabel>Source</guilabel> tab."
msgstr ""
"Odprite pogovorno okno za snemanje in izberite zavihek <guilabel>Vir</"
"guilabel>."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:6366
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;<command>start_now</command>"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;<command>start_now</command>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:6367
#, no-c-format
msgid "Open the recording dialog and directly start recording."
msgstr "Odprite pogovorno okno za snemanje in neposredno začnite snemati."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6385
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_reverse; (Reverse)"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_reverse; (Reverse - Vzvratno)"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:6389
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_reverse;"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_reverse;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6398
#, no-c-format
msgid "This simple effect reverses the content of the current selection."
msgstr "Ta preprost učinek obrne vsebino trenutnega izbora."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6407
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_samplerate; (Sample Rate Conversion)"
msgstr ""
"&no-i18n-plugin_samplerate; (Sample Rate Conversion - Pretvorba hitrosti "
"vzorčenja)"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:6411
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_samplerate;"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_samplerate;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6420
#, no-c-format
msgid "Changes the sample rate of the current selection or the whole signal."
msgstr "Spremeni hitrost vzorčenja trenutnega izbora ali celotnega signala."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6431
#, no-c-format
msgid "new rate"
msgstr "nova stopnja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6433
#, no-c-format
msgid "The new sample rate in samples per second (floating point value)."
msgstr ""
"Nova hitrost vzorčenja v vzorcih na sekundo (vrednost s plavajočo vejico)."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:6440
#, no-c-format
msgid "<replaceable>mode</replaceable> (optional)"
msgstr "<replaceable>način</replaceable> (neobvezno)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6442
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this parameter is used and set to the value \"<literal>all</literal>\", "
"then this effect will be applied to the whole signal. Otherwise it will be "
"applied to the current selection only."
msgstr ""
"Če je ta parameter uporabljen in nastavljen na vrednost \"<literal>all</"
"literal>\", bo ta učinek uporabljen za celoten signal. V nasprotnem primeru "
"bo uporabljen samo za trenutno izbiro."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6458
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_saveblocks; (Save Blocks)"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_saveblocks; (Save Blocks - Shrani bloke)"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:6466
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the Save Blocks Plugin"
msgstr "Posnetek zaslona vtičnika Save Blocks"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:6473
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_saveblocks;"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_saveblocks;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6482
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Saves all sections between markers, each into a separate file. Each file is "
"given a name that can be customized by using a pattern that can contain the "
"original file name, an index and the number of sections."
msgstr ""
"Shrani vse razdelke med označevaniki, vsakega v ločeno datoteko. Vsaka "
"datoteka ima ime, ki ga je mogoče prilagoditi z uporabo vzorca, ki lahko "
"vsebuje izvirno ime datoteke, indeks in število odsekov."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6488
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is also allowed that the file name pattern contains forward slashes as "
"path separators, which allows saving the sections into different sub "
"directories. Please note that all whitespace characters around such path "
"separators are silently removed, to avoid creation of directory names which "
"begin or end with a whitespace."
msgstr ""
"Dovoljeno je tudi, da vzorec imena datoteke vsebuje poševnice kot ločila "
"poti, kar omogoča shranjevanje odsekov v različne podimenike. Upoštevajte, "
"da so vsi presledki okrog takšnih ločil poti tiho odstranjeni, da se "
"prepreči ustvarjanje imen imenikov, ki se začnejo ali končajo s presledkom."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6505
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A pattern that will be used for creating the names of the files. It can "
"contain the following wildcards which will be replaced by the corresponding "
"content when creating the final file name:"
msgstr ""
"Vzorec, ki bo uporabljen za ustvarjanje imen datotek. Vsebuje lahko "
"naslednje nadomestne znake, ki bodo pri ustvarjanju končnega imena datoteke "
"nadomeščeni z ustrezno vsebino:"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:6522
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;<command>[%nr]</command>"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;<command>[%nr]</command>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:6523
#, no-c-format
msgid "Will be replaced with the current index of the file to save."
msgstr "Zamenjan bo s trenutnim indeksom datoteke za shranjevanje."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:6529
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;<command>[%count]</command>"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;<command>[%count]</command>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:6530
#, no-c-format
msgid "Will be replaced with the number of sections that will be saved."
msgstr "Zamenjalo se bo s številom odsekov, ki bodo shranjeni."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:6536
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;<command>[%total]</command>"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;<command>[%total]</command>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:6537
#, no-c-format
msgid "Will be replaced with the index of the last file to save."
msgstr "Nadomeščen bo z indeksom zadnje datoteke za shranjevanje."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:6543
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;<command>[%filename]</command>"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;<command>[%filename]</command>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:6544
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Will be replaced with the base file name, without path and without extension."
msgstr ""
"Zamenjalo se bo z osnovnim imenom datoteke, brez poti in brez končnice."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:6550
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&no-i18n-tag;<command>[%fileinfo{<replaceable>keyword</replaceable>}]</"
"command>"
msgstr ""
"&no-i18n-tag;<command>[%fileinfo{<replaceable>ključna beseda</"
"replaceable>}]</command>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:6551
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Will be replaced with the content of a file information identified by "
"<replaceable>keyword</replaceable>. See section <link linkend=\"file-info-"
"list\" endterm=\"file-info-list-title\"></link> for a list of all available "
"keywords."
msgstr ""
"Zamenjana bo z vsebino podatkov o datoteki, označenih s <replaceable>ključno "
"besedo</replaceable>. Oglejte si razdelek <link linkend=\"file-info-list\" "
"endterm=\"file-info-list-title\"></link> za seznam vseh razpoložljivih "
"ključnih besed."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6574
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All numeric wildcards can also contain a numerical argument after the "
"\"<literal>%</literal>\" and the identifier, to force a certain number of "
"digits. If the number is preceded by a <literal>0</literal> then the result "
"will contain leading zeroes, otherwise it will contain leading spaces."
msgstr ""
"Vsi številski nadomestni znaki lahko vsebujejo tudi številski argument za "
"\"<literal>%</literal>\" in identifikatorjem, da vsilijo določeno število "
"števk. Če je pred številom <literal>0</literal>, bo rezultat vseboval "
"začetne ničle, sicer bo vseboval začetne presledke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6581
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Example: <command><literal>[%04nr]</literal></command> produces a number "
"between 0001 and 9999."
msgstr ""
"Primer: <command><literal>[%04nr]</literal></command> ustvari številko med "
"0001 in 9999."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6589
#, no-c-format
msgid "numbering mode"
msgstr "način številčenja"

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6625
#, no-c-format
msgid "extension"
msgstr "podaljšek"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6627
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The file name extension to use for the saved blocks. This determines what "
"encoding is used."
msgstr ""
"Končnica imena datoteke, ki se uporablja za shranjene bloke. To določa, "
"katero kodiranje se uporablja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6637
#, no-c-format
msgid "The location to export the saved blocks."
msgstr "Lokacija za izvoz shranjenih blokov."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6683
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_selectrange; (Select Range)"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_selectrange; (Select Range - Izberi obseg)"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:6691
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the Select Range Plugin"
msgstr "Posnetek zaslona vtičnika Select Range"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:6698
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_selectrange;"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_selectrange;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6707
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Shows a dialog to select a range of samples. The start and the length of the "
"selection can be set either by a time in milliseconds, in samples, or as a "
"percentage of the total length of the file."
msgstr ""
"Prikaže pogovorno okno za izbiro obsega vzorcev. Začetek in dolžino izbire "
"lahko nastavite s časom v milisekundah, v vzorcih ali kot odstotek skupne "
"dolžine datoteke."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6719
#, no-c-format
msgid "start mode"
msgstr "začetni način"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6721
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Determines the units in which the <emphasis>start</emphasis> of the "
"selection will be given."
msgstr "Določa enote, v katerih bo podan <emphasis>začetek</emphasis> izbora."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:6736 index.docbook:7136
#, no-c-format
msgid "milliseconds"
msgstr "milisekund"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:6740 index.docbook:7140
#, no-c-format
msgid "samples"
msgstr "vzorcev"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:6744 index.docbook:7144
#, no-c-format
msgid "percentage of the length of the file"
msgstr "odstotek dolžine datoteke"

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6754
#, no-c-format
msgid "range mode"
msgstr "način dosega"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6756
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Determines the units in which the <emphasis>length</emphasis> of the "
"selection will be given. See the description if the parameter "
"<parameter>start mode</parameter> for a list of possible values."
msgstr ""
"Določa enote, v katerih bo podana <emphasis>dolžina</emphasis> izbora. "
"Glejte opis parametra <parameter>način zagona</parameter> za seznam možnih "
"vrednosti."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6768
#, no-c-format
msgid "start"
msgstr "začetek"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6770
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The start of the selection, in milliseconds, samples or percentage of the "
"length of the file, depending on the parameter <parameter>range mode</"
"parameter>."
msgstr ""
"Začetek izbire, v milisekundah, vzorcih ali odstotkih dolžine datoteke, "
"odvisno od parametra <parameter>range mode</parameter>."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:6780 index.docbook:7153
#, no-c-format
msgid "length"
msgstr "dolžina"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6782
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The length of the selection, in milliseconds, samples or percentage of the "
"length of the file, depending on the parameter <parameter>range mode</"
"parameter>."
msgstr ""
"Dolžina izbire v milisekundah, vzorcih ali odstotkih dolžine datoteke, "
"odvisno od parametra <parameter>range mode</parameter>."

